    <item>
      <title>Directed Graphs in Agent Orchestration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/directed-graphs-in-agent-orchestration/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/directed-graphs-in-agent-orchestration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In agent orchestration, the &lt;a href=&#34;../terms/directed-graph.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;directed graph&lt;/a&gt; serves as the explicit representation of control flow. Each node is a processing step — a function, an LLM call, a tool invocation — and each edge defines when one step follows another. Conditional edges, taken only when a predicate on the graph state is true, enable branching. Subgraphs enable modular composition. The graph structure makes the execution topology inspectable and debuggable in a way that imperative code loops are not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Endeavor Discharge and Zeno Dynamics</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/endeavor-discharge-and-zeno-dynamics/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/endeavor-discharge-and-zeno-dynamics/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;discharge-condition&#34;&gt;Discharge condition&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;At history &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;t_0&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, an endeavor has aim &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∈&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g \in H_{t_0}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; with &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;∉&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msubsup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∗&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msubsup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g \notin H^*_{t_0}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the aim is present but unsettled. The saturation gap &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;[&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;σ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;]&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;[g, \sigma_{t_0}(g)]&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the backward deficit (the past has not fully constituted &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;). The transfer gap &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;[&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;Δ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;]&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;[g, \Delta_{t_0}(g)]&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the forward deficit (&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is not yet carried by every forward extension).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The endeavor is discharged at terminal history &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;t_1&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; iff &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∈&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msubsup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∗&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msubsup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;σ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∩&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;Δ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g \in H^*_{t_1} = \mathrm{Fix}(\sigma_{t_1}) \cap \mathrm{Fix}(\Delta_{t_1})&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;: both gaps closed.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The agent&amp;rsquo;s striving does not modify the nuclei. &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;σ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\sigma_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;Δ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\Delta_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; at any history are structural features of the presheaf &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. What the agent controls is which steps to take, traversing the path &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;t_0 \to t_1&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. The nuclei at each history along the path are determined by the presheaf, not by the agent.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Nuclear Functions</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/nuclear-functions/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/nuclear-functions/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In the relational universe &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;bold&#34;&gt;S&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;bold&#34;&gt;h&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;J&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;R = \mathbf{Sh}(T, J)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, a function between presheaves &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⇒&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f : A \Rightarrow B&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a natural transformation — a family of fiber-level maps &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f_t : A(t) \to B(t)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; indexed by histories &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∈&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;t \in T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, satisfying the naturality condition: for every morphism &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;g : t&amp;#x27; \to t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;T&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34; display=&#34;block&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∘&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f_{t&amp;#x27;} \circ A(g) = B(g) \circ f_t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;Restricting an element from &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;t&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; to &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;t&amp;#x27;&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and then applying &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; gives the same result as applying &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;f&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; first and then restricting. A family of maps that fails naturality is path-dependent — it depends on which history is used to observe the element. Such a family is not a function between presheaves; it is an inconsistent collection of local maps.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Posets and Categories in the Semiotic Universe</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/posets-and-categories-in-the-semiotic-universe/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/posets-and-categories-in-the-semiotic-universe/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The semiotic universe&amp;rsquo;s history object (H, ≤) is a thin category — a &lt;a href=&#34;../domains/objects/domains/posets/terms/partial-order.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;partial order&lt;/a&gt; viewed as a &lt;a href=&#34;../domains/objects/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/category.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;category&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=&#34;../domains/objects/domains/categories/domains/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;morphism&lt;/a&gt; from a to b is the unique witness that a ≤ b. There is at most one morphism between any two objects, and its existence expresses the ordering relation.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Heyting algebra H is a &lt;a href=&#34;../domains/objects/domains/posets/terms/lattice.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;complete lattice&lt;/a&gt; with the Heyting implication — the algebraic structure underlying the semiotic universe. Its elements are semantic values and its ordering expresses entailment: a ≤ b means &amp;ldquo;a entails b.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Survey: Lean 4 vs Agda for Relationality Formalization</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/lean-agda-survey/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/lean-agda-survey/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;survey-lean-4-vs-agda-for-relationality-formalization&#34;&gt;Survey: Lean 4 vs Agda for Relationality Formalization&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Survey of the two proof assistants available in this environment for formalizing&#xA;the mathematical structures underlying relationality and the semioverse hierarchy.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;environment&#34;&gt;Environment&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;thead&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Tool&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Version&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Library&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Status&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;  &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Lean 4&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;4.17.0 (via elan)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Mathlib4 (latest)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Working, builds with cache&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Agda&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;2.6.3&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;agda-stdlib&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Working, pre-installed&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Both tools are functional. Lean requires &lt;code&gt;~/.elan/bin&lt;/code&gt; on PATH and downloads&#xA;~2 GB of Mathlib cache on first use. Agda works out of the box.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Introducing relational Dynamics</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/introducing-relational-dynamics/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 02 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/introducing-relational-dynamics/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Imagine asking not “what is this thing?” but instead, “what has to be happening for this to keep going?” That shift in perspective is the heart of relational dynamics: a way of paying attention that treats everything as held together by relations.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Think of any ordinary situation: a conversation, a school club, even a stone sitting on a desk. None of these things persist on their own. A conversation continues only if turns keep being taken and understood. A club continues only if meetings are called, rooms are opened, members show up. Even the stone continues only because gravity, friction, and a surface hold it there. What exists, exists through relating.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/acts-of-relationality/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/acts-of-relationality/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Acts Narrative&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Lossless aggregation of all act documents. Ordered by dependency walk seeded at relationlessness when resolvable, then remaining acts topologically. Each section embeds the original file verbatim.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Being Relationless (Relationlessness)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Path: docs/math/acts/relationlessness.md&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Status: release&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Slug: relationlessness&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Original&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;---&#xD;&#xA;title: Being Relationless&#xD;&#xA;act: Relationlessness&#xD;&#xA;slug: relationlessness&#xD;&#xA;top: null&#xD;&#xA;bottom: null&#xD;&#xA;summary: &amp;gt;-&#xD;&#xA;  We begin with nothing but the absence of relation; acknowledging that&#xD;&#xA;  absence fixes the empty act as our initial reference point.&#xD;&#xA;layer: act&#xD;&#xA;status: release&#xD;&#xA;tags:&#xD;&#xA;  - act&#xD;&#xA;---&#xD;&#xA;# Being Relationless&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;## Interpretation&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;We begin with nothing but the absence of relation; acknowledging that absence fixes the empty act as our initial reference point.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;No recognitions precede this step, so the empty tree `()` is the only permissible trace.  Naming that trace *Relationlessness* therefore records, without additional assumptions, that we start from the undifferentiated void.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;{{ act_info(page.meta) }}&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;{{ act_nav(page.meta) }}&#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Excluding (Exclude)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Path: docs/math/acts/exclude.md&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Status: release&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Top: Relationlessness&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Bottom: Relationlessness&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Slug: exclude&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Original&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Absorbing Closure</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/absorb-closure/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/absorb-closure/</guid>
      <description>Closure-like nuclei absorb meets: x meet ν(y) collapses inside ν(x meet y). &lt;em&gt;Nucleate&lt;/em&gt; witnessing &lt;em&gt;Meet Recognition&lt;/em&gt; yields &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Absorb Closure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;code&gt;AbsorbClosure&lt;/code&gt;).</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>On Relationality</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/on-relationality/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/texts/on-relationality/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;on-relationality&#34;&gt;On Relationality&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;A trace of the reductive tension of nothing&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The question &amp;ldquo;Why does anything exist at all?&amp;rdquo; smuggles in two opposing recognitions: &lt;em&gt;Relating&lt;/em&gt; (to ask) and &lt;em&gt;Not Relating&lt;/em&gt; (to deny). These recognitions cannot both vanish, so the trace below simply records the acts forced by resolving that tension. Each subsequent section earns a new act by showing how it necessarily follows from the previous one.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;style-guide&#34;&gt;Style Guide&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In text, &lt;em&gt;Relational Terms&lt;/em&gt; are written in &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong Emphasized Title Case&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; when they are being defined, and &lt;em&gt;Emphasize Title Case&lt;/em&gt; when they are being referenced, with a parentheticized &lt;code&gt;MonospacePascalCase&lt;/code&gt; representation of how they will be used in our relational expression format. For example, &amp;ldquo;A &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relational Term&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;code&gt;RelationalTerm&lt;/code&gt;) is symbol used to represent a &lt;em&gt;Recognition&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;rdquo; After being defined in prose, the term must be given concretely in a code block.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
